&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REGISTERED NURSE – ALVERSTONE and LUCCOMBE&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FULL TIME (37.5 HOURS) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£24,907-£30,615 (Band 5)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated Registered Nurse to join our forward thinking team on Alverstone and Luccombe. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be committed to going the extra mile and passionate about ensuring high standards of care are delivered to your patients. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant must have an interest in trauma and emergency surgery, must be hard working, with good communication skills and be able to work well in a team. Individuals must be motivated, enthusiastic and reliable. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post involves working with all members of the multi-disciplinary team and you will need to be organised, dynamic and able to prioritise your workload.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Individuals applying for this post will also be responsible and accountable for leading a team on a shift and for providing an excellent standard of individualised patient centered care. Support and supervision of Health Care Assistants and Student Nurses is also a requirement of this post. A mentorship qualification would be advantageous.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details or an informal visit please contact Sister Nicola Moore on 01983 534711 or Sister Heidi Meekins on 01983 534717.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
